snippet.textDisplay:
Few years back on a sunny morning I boarded Ispat Express from Sambalpur. The train was jam packed so like others I chose to stand for the entire journey. After the train started to run, my eyes fell upon an old man who was standing very close to me, he was the singer of this legendary song , Jitendra Haripal. 
I got down at Rourkela and he was still standing waiting for a seat... seems like the Rangabati team finally got a tribute...

snippet.textDisplay:
Well after hearing to this masterpiece my thoughts are as follows:

1. Massive massive massive respect to Shri Jitendra Haripal & Shri Krishna Patel; the original artistes of the song. The way they carried out the song, it still feels so fresh even after 4 decades !

2. Kudos to Ram Sampath and team for re-recreating such a brilliant masterpiece. We must note that they have done a fabulous job in "promoting" the rich cultural heritage of Odisha.

3. And "yes", when you promote something your base intention is to reach masses (as much as possible) and the artistes do research as to how certain words/syllables should be pronounced so that more and more audience could get it and connect to it

4. Tamil rap is simply awesome and Tony/Rajesh have done a fabulous job. Beautifully written and sung. Regarding need for it ? I suppose it "is" needed. Reason ? Not known to many, but Odisha is continental in many regards w.r.t food we eat (neither very hot nor very mild), clothes we wear (we still find dhotis being worn by our grand dads whereas our fathers are perfectly comfortable with Lungis while we in Bermudas :) ), traditions we follow (each section of Odisha has a variety of cultural disaporas and a lot to offer). Also does any really know that Western Odisha does have a sizeable population of Tamils living. Anyway, coming to the point, I feel if you need to promote something and want people to accept and cherish your culture, we need to do the same and that's when we know more and respect more

All in all fab attempt by all and yes let's not fiddle with the joy this song has brought us !!! Rangabati...Rangabati :)
